<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Terra Classic community members are mulling a =
revival of the network=E2=80=99s failed terraUSD (USTC) token nearly a year=
 after Terra=E2=80=99s implosion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Terra Classic is the original network created =
by Terraform Labs. It has continued as an independent blockchain rather tha=
n Terra 2.0, which is a forked version that was created in the wake of Terr=
a's collapse.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In discussions that started in mid-April, comm=
unity members are describing a model that relies on token buybacks, unidire=
ctional swaps, staking and an =E2=80=9Calgorithmic peg divergence fee=E2=80=
=9D to address the issues with the original design.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When the TerraUSD stablecoin=C2=A0collapsed la=
st May, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31339354.2=
58432/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtM=
